    <abstract>
      <t>   This document first describes an architecture of Content-based
   Service Router (CSR), which is used to exchange service prefixes and
   topology information based on distributed routing protocol, and
   optimize routing based on service prefixes and topology, as one
   important component of Distributed Micro Service Communication (DMSC)
   architecture.

